transcripts.text: Who will buy this wonderful lonely world Such a sky you never did see?  Who will buy my sweet red rose?  Who will tie it up with a ribbon And put it in a box for me?  Thank you, God, for a lovely day and for bringing Daddy home.  Please don't take Daddy away again, ever.  Who will buy this wonderful feeling?  I'm so high, I swear I could fly.  I don't want to lose it, so what am I to do?  To keep the sky so blue, there must be someone who...
